WEBVTT

00:02.080 --> 00:03.514
NARRATOR:
Previously on Revolution:

00:04.000 --> 00:06.037
CHARLIE:
I've never left the Monroe Republic.

00:06.320 --> 00:08.436
MILES:
Georgia Federation. Whole different world.

00:08.600 --> 00:11.479
- Madame President.
FOSTER: I want you and your rebels...

00:11.640 --> 00:13.597
...to hit Monroe from the inside.

00:13.760 --> 00:15.273
Open up a second front.

00:15.960 --> 00:19.191
JANE: Why would you go to the Tower?
- We need to turn the power back on.

00:19.360 --> 00:21.715
This will tell you everything
you need to know.

00:21.880 --> 00:24.349
Dr. Warren's little diary
making any sense?

00:24.520 --> 00:26.318
RACHEL:
It's gonna take a while to translate.

00:26.480 --> 00:28.198
Come on out!
Just you, me and Emma.

00:28.360 --> 00:29.680
You wanna see Miles?

00:29.880 --> 00:31.279
[WHIMPERING]
No, not Miles!

00:31.440 --> 00:32.953
My son. Your son.

00:33.120 --> 00:34.155
Where is he?

00:34.320 --> 00:36.516
MAN: Major Neville and his wife
fled the city last night.

00:36.720 --> 00:40.998
- Why would he do that?
MAN: Our spies have spotted his son, Jason.

00:41.160 --> 00:43.595
- His son's dead.
MAN: He's with the rebels now.

00:43.800 --> 00:45.757
MONROE: Wonder what else
he's been lying about.

00:45.920 --> 00:47.069
Torn-

00:48.000 --> 00:50.389
I hope you're ready
to get back into action.

01:13.600 --> 01:14.954
[DOOR OPENS]

01:25.600 --> 01:26.749
[DOOR OPENS]

01:28.520 --> 01:29.794
[GRUNTS]

01:42.000 --> 01:43.798
No! No! No!

01:43.960 --> 01:45.280
[GRUNTING]

02:16.400 --> 02:18.391
I gotta say, Pete...

02:20.320 --> 02:22.550
...I thought I trained you better than this.

02:26.560 --> 02:28.471
You let that guy capture you?

02:31.720 --> 02:33.711
What am I supposed to do with you?

02:34.280 --> 02:35.953
You could let me go.

02:36.120 --> 02:38.919
So I should show you mercy.

02:41.920 --> 02:43.991
That what Monroe's doing?

02:45.760 --> 02:47.433
Is he showing me mercy?

02:51.480 --> 02:52.834
No.

02:54.920 --> 02:57.594
Monroe is a rabid dog.

02:59.240 --> 03:01.436
And he's only getting worse.

03:03.720 --> 03:05.677
So I'm gonna put him down...

03:08.080 --> 03:10.799
...and God help anybody
who gets in my way.

03:12.840 --> 03:15.753
Now, I'm gonna ask you
one last time, Pete.

03:16.840 --> 03:19.116
You gonna tell me what you know...

03:20.320 --> 03:22.152
...or are you in my way too?

03:26.200 --> 03:28.032
I'm not a traitor.

03:29.880 --> 03:31.996
[CHUCKLES]

03:32.160 --> 03:34.071
Like you said...

03:35.480 --> 03:37.869
...you trained me better than that.

03:45.400 --> 03:47.516
Bag or no bag?

03:49.960 --> 03:51.598
No bag.

04:14.920 --> 04:15.955
[GUNSHOT]

04:35.960 --> 04:37.553
TIM:
Sir.

04:37.880 --> 04:40.110
Georgian reinforcements are here.

04:41.040 --> 04:42.360
What reinforcements?

04:44.040 --> 04:45.235
Mine.

04:47.040 --> 04:48.075
Oh.

04:48.240 --> 04:49.674
Easy there, Tex.

04:51.160 --> 04:53.390
This is a letter...

04:53.600 --> 04:55.034
...I'm reaching for.

05:00.440 --> 05:02.954
- What is it?
- It's from President Foster.

05:03.160 --> 05:06.312
Check the seal. It's legit.

05:08.160 --> 05:13.678
I, uh, hate to see your lips move
while you read, so I'll paraphrase.

05:14.320 --> 05:20.157
I am now a commissioned officer
of the Georgia Federation.

05:21.000 --> 05:22.354
You gotta be kidding me.

05:22.560 --> 05:25.439
Now we're partners, Miles.

05:26.560 --> 05:29.552
Tom, I'm gonna kill you.

05:29.800 --> 05:31.757
Foster won't like it.

05:32.120 --> 05:35.317
Yeah, well, I don't take orders from her.

05:35.520 --> 05:37.272
I certainly don't take them from you.

05:37.480 --> 05:41.439
True. But she has provided
your adorable rebel cause...

05:41.600 --> 05:44.592
...with a steady stream of men and guns.

05:45.360 --> 05:48.318
If you don't work with me,
I'll take it all back.

05:48.480 --> 05:52.599
And you can go back
to being the general of my nuts.

05:57.960 --> 05:59.473
Besides...

06:01.000 --> 06:03.230
...we've got an important job to do.

06:04.000 --> 06:05.479
Nothing's that important.

06:05.640 --> 06:07.711
Monroe is weaponizing anthrax.

06:09.600 --> 06:12.638
Oh, do I have your attention now?

06:15.200 --> 06:17.476
<i>One Dr. Ethan Camp.</i>

06:17.680 --> 06:20.991
<i>He's in charge of the program.
They can't make it without him.</i>

06:23.480 --> 06:24.754
So wanna go get him?

06:38.480 --> 06:39.515
CHARLIE:
Come on, Neville?

06:39.680 --> 06:42.513
After everything he's done to us,
we should shoot the son of a bitch.

06:42.680 --> 06:43.715
Take it easy.

06:43.920 --> 06:47.675
She's right. Even if Neville doesn't screw
us over, even if we get this Dr. Camp...

06:47.880 --> 06:50.759
-...what are we gonna do with him?
- Get him to Georgia.

06:50.920 --> 06:53.150
So President Foster
can get her hands on the guy?

06:53.320 --> 06:54.594
Start making her own anthrax?

06:54.760 --> 06:57.229
MILES:
If it's gonna help us stop Monroe, yes.

06:57.440 --> 07:00.717
And since when
did this become a democracy, hmm?

07:00.880 --> 07:03.315
You two, get in line or stay here.

07:11.480 --> 07:13.357
TOM:
Ladies.

07:13.560 --> 07:15.358
After you.

07:20.480 --> 07:22.676
Just couldn't keep away, could you?

07:28.680 --> 07:31.832
My name is Captain Richard Lucas
of the Georgian navy...

07:32.040 --> 07:34.077
...and this is my steamboat.

07:34.280 --> 07:36.669
It is my job to get you
in and out of Parkersburg...

07:36.840 --> 07:38.911
...and back over the border alive.

07:40.920 --> 07:42.638
[MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

07:47.240 --> 07:49.914
RICHARD: Now, as far as anyone knows,
this is a fishing vessel...

07:50.120 --> 07:53.909
...so if you just keep your heads down
and do whatever the hell I tell you...

07:54.200 --> 07:56.589
...we'll get along just fine.

08:08.400 --> 08:10.391
[CHATTERING]

08:18.040 --> 08:22.238
CURT: Look, even if you had anything
I want, which you don't, we're not trading.

08:22.400 --> 08:27.190
Please. We haven't eaten in four days.
We'll take anything.

08:27.440 --> 08:29.909
Weather's cold, food's scarce.

08:30.120 --> 08:32.270
If I was you, I'd head south.

08:33.080 --> 08:34.673
RACHEL:
We can't.

08:35.080 --> 08:36.354
We have to go west.

08:37.039 --> 08:39.839
Folks, I feel for you, I do.

08:40.000 --> 08:42.674
But any food I give you
is food I can't give my kids.

08:43.520 --> 08:46.399
So I'm sorry, but we're done.

08:53.320 --> 08:55.834
Now, go on, get out of here.

09:12.440 --> 09:15.353
Look, I know we've had our issues...

09:15.520 --> 09:17.557
...but we're on the same side.

09:18.440 --> 09:20.192
How about we call a truce?

09:26.840 --> 09:29.116
You forget, I know you, Dad.

09:33.440 --> 09:35.556
I get why you're with Georgia now.

09:37.720 --> 09:39.358
Why's that?

09:41.520 --> 09:45.400
You don't care what side you're on
as long as they kiss your ass.

09:47.040 --> 09:51.398
I'm with Georgia
because you are a traitor.

09:51.560 --> 09:56.031
Your mother and I had to escape
in the night like criminals.

09:56.600 --> 09:58.637
She got hypothermia...

09:58.800 --> 10:02.156
...almost died because of you.

10:03.280 --> 10:07.194
You selfish little prick.

10:08.600 --> 10:12.912
This is what we had to do to survive.

10:15.760 --> 10:17.831
Is that okay with you?

10:45.080 --> 10:47.196
What are you saying, Mr. Flynn?

10:47.360 --> 10:50.955
I'm only asking you
to consider the bigger picture.

10:51.720 --> 10:56.430
Your methods have been a tiny bit...
severe lately.

10:58.360 --> 11:01.796
I can't imagine why I'm so upset.

11:02.320 --> 11:06.678
The goal is to stop the insurgents,
not radicalize more of them.

11:07.840 --> 11:09.558
Are the rebels pulling their punches?

11:10.280 --> 11:11.839
Or Georgia?

11:12.480 --> 11:13.800
We have to do whatever it takes.

11:13.960 --> 11:17.476
If that means anthrax or one of these
new toys you've been building, so be it.

11:17.640 --> 11:19.631
Right, because that'll show Matheson.

11:24.560 --> 11:26.471
Oh, Mr. Flynn, heh.

11:28.200 --> 11:30.237
You're my IT 9W-

11:31.840 --> 11:36.471
If you say something like that again,
I'm gonna rip your throat out.

11:37.080 --> 11:38.673
Is that clear?

11:47.160 --> 11:49.993
We dock in 10. And then you're on.

11:50.800 --> 11:52.359
We're on? You're not coming?

11:52.680 --> 11:54.478
Not my style.

12:00.200 --> 12:02.077
We're better off without him.

12:23.840 --> 12:25.831
[GRUNTS]

12:35.640 --> 12:36.675
No! No! No!

12:36.840 --> 12:38.831
[GRUNTING]

12:39.640 --> 12:41.790
[EXPLOSION]

12:44.880 --> 12:47.269
Now, that wasn't so hard, was it?

13:05.760 --> 13:07.398
Whoa.

13:08.440 --> 13:10.829
I think you took something of ours.

13:12.160 --> 13:14.071
What are you talking about?

13:14.280 --> 13:17.238
Lady, lying's only gonna make it worse.

13:25.520 --> 13:27.716
We're sorry, we're just hungry.

13:28.000 --> 13:30.753
Stealing food means
one of my own starves.

13:39.080 --> 13:40.354
On your knees.

13:41.040 --> 13:42.553
Wait, what?

13:42.800 --> 13:46.191
This is hard country. No matter the crime,
there's only one punishment.

13:46.400 --> 13:48.835
- Come on, man.
- I said, on your knees.

13:51.240 --> 13:53.277
[GASPS]

13:59.160 --> 14:00.230
[GRUNTS]

14:00.440 --> 14:01.953
[HORSE NEIGHS]

14:02.720 --> 14:04.154
Since when do you have a gun?

14:05.720 --> 14:07.438
Since Miles gave it to me.

14:07.600 --> 14:09.671
Come on. They're gonna be coming.

14:23.960 --> 14:25.314
MAN:
Let's go.

14:30.920 --> 14:32.274
[YELLS]

14:34.000 --> 14:35.354
[GRUNTING]

14:35.560 --> 14:37.198
AARON:
Rachel!

14:37.360 --> 14:39.351
[RACHEL GROANING]

14:43.600 --> 14:45.955
What happened? Let me see.

14:46.400 --> 14:47.435
[GASPS]

14:49.640 --> 14:51.039
It's okay.

15:17.200 --> 15:19.350
Last year or two...

15:19.760 --> 15:24.357
...Sebastian's been recruiting them
younger and dumber.

15:25.480 --> 15:27.756
So may I say...

15:27.960 --> 15:31.794
...it is a pleasure working
with a true professional again.

15:32.720 --> 15:34.757
We make a hell of a team.

15:43.280 --> 15:44.315
[DOOR OPENS]

15:45.200 --> 15:46.634
Sir.

15:47.480 --> 15:48.993
Doc's waking up.

15:55.160 --> 15:56.992
Mazel tov, doc.

15:57.360 --> 15:59.670
You have been liberated
by the Georgia Federation.

16:04.120 --> 16:05.315
Please let me go.

16:05.840 --> 16:07.513
No can do.

16:07.880 --> 16:12.113
You have been making
some nasty bugs for Monroe.

16:12.320 --> 16:14.550
And in a world short of penicillin?

16:14.720 --> 16:18.350
He's keeping my family
under guard 24/7.

16:19.200 --> 16:21.271
TOM: I wouldn't worry.
ETHAN: You don't understand.

16:21.440 --> 16:26.310
As soon as they realize I'm gone,
they're gonna kill my wife. My daughter.

16:27.520 --> 16:29.511
MILES:
Monroe doesn't have your family anymore.

16:30.360 --> 16:31.395
We do.

16:32.440 --> 16:34.795
While I was freeing you...

16:35.600 --> 16:37.432
...he was freeing them.

16:38.760 --> 16:40.876
- Aah!
- You're coming with us.

16:41.040 --> 16:43.031
[SCREAMING AND CRYING]

16:44.840 --> 16:46.478
<i>MILES:
You're welcome, by the way.</i>

16:47.440 --> 16:49.351
- Where are they?
MILES: They're safe.

16:50.040 --> 16:51.917
On another boat.

16:52.560 --> 16:54.358
ETHAN:
All right, when can I see them?

16:54.560 --> 16:55.834
You can't.

16:58.040 --> 17:00.554
What do you mean? I don't understand.

17:00.720 --> 17:02.711
If you're cooperative...

17:02.880 --> 17:04.951
...maybe we'll set up a visit
down the road.

17:05.560 --> 17:06.595
Cooperative?

17:06.760 --> 17:10.435
After you do the important work for Georgia
that you've been doing for Monroe.

17:10.640 --> 17:12.676
Look, I'm begging, let my family go.

17:12.920 --> 17:14.877
We'll disappear.

17:15.079 --> 17:16.400
We'll go to Texas.

17:17.560 --> 17:19.994
You're gonna do exactly what we say...

17:20.160 --> 17:22.992
...or you're never gonna see
your family again, you understand?

17:31.320 --> 17:33.436
You knew about this the whole time.

17:42.400 --> 17:44.391
[RACHEL GROANING]

17:53.120 --> 17:54.349
[RACHEL SHRIEKS]

17:54.520 --> 17:56.511
AARON:
Okay, easy, easy, easy, shh.

18:05.760 --> 18:08.229
So we kidnap people now?
That's what we do?

18:10.680 --> 18:11.829
We don't have a choice.

18:14.120 --> 18:15.190
I'm leaving.

18:16.920 --> 18:19.639
Soon as we get to shore,
I'm transferring to another unit.

18:25.240 --> 18:26.913
If that's what you want.

18:28.040 --> 18:29.951
When you found me...

18:30.720 --> 18:32.757
...asked me to help you find Danny...

18:34.680 --> 18:37.149
...I came because I thought you changed.

18:40.160 --> 18:41.559
Anyway...

18:42.480 --> 18:43.959
...I was wrong.

18:49.720 --> 18:53.350
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

18:53.520 --> 18:56.353
- Please stop. Stop.
- I'm sorry. I've never done this before.

18:56.520 --> 18:57.840
RACHEL: Please don't!
AARON: Okay.

18:58.000 --> 19:00.992
[RACHEL GROANING]

19:01.520 --> 19:04.911
Oh, oh, uh, okay, okay, okay.

19:05.120 --> 19:07.509
I think I got it put back in, uh...

19:09.400 --> 19:11.357
I'm gonna splint it now.

19:12.200 --> 19:14.191
Don't bother.

19:14.520 --> 19:16.591
They're gonna be coming.
You need to leave.

19:16.800 --> 19:18.837
- You need to get out now.
- Rachel, no.

19:19.000 --> 19:23.710
Look at my leg. Look at it, I'm already dead.
We both know that. Go.

19:23.920 --> 19:26.150
You need to take the book. No.

19:26.320 --> 19:28.118
You need to take Warren's journal...

19:28.280 --> 19:29.714
-...to the Tower.
- Rachel, stop.

19:29.880 --> 19:33.714
- There's something that I need to tell you.
- Just stop. I'm not leaving you.

19:34.480 --> 19:36.073
You wouldn't leave me.

19:39.960 --> 19:41.792
I would leave you.

19:43.320 --> 19:45.231
This is more important.

19:45.440 --> 19:47.716
Please, Rachel, I--

19:48.400 --> 19:51.472
- I don't wanna do this alone.
- You would rather die here with me...

19:51.640 --> 19:52.755
...than be left alone?

19:53.840 --> 19:57.879
You walked out on your wife,
why is it so hard to leave me?

20:03.240 --> 20:07.757
You're just saying all of this to try to make
me wanna leave and it's not gonna work.

20:08.760 --> 20:10.671
I'm not going anywhere.

20:15.960 --> 20:18.634
[WHIMPERING]
Please.

20:20.400 --> 20:21.470
Please.

20:34.800 --> 20:36.871
CHARLIE:
I brought you some water.

20:41.360 --> 20:42.794
[ETHAN COUGHS]

20:43.840 --> 20:44.989
Why are you doing this?

20:46.160 --> 20:47.389
This is not me.

20:48.360 --> 20:49.839
How is it not you?

20:51.160 --> 20:52.639
Look...

20:53.080 --> 20:55.310
...my daughter's name is Bonnie.

20:55.960 --> 20:57.871
She's just 11.

20:58.280 --> 21:00.510
She's gotta be so scared.

21:02.800 --> 21:03.949
Please.

21:04.960 --> 21:06.951
[SIREN WAILING]

21:09.160 --> 21:12.551
- What is that? No! No! No!
- Shh, shh, shh.

21:13.560 --> 21:16.552
[MAN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

21:34.040 --> 21:35.110
Routine inspection.

21:36.040 --> 21:37.189
Hopefully.

21:37.840 --> 21:39.069
We gotta get below deck.

21:39.840 --> 21:42.958
No sudden moves. Just stay cool.

21:53.920 --> 21:55.069
What are you doing?

21:55.240 --> 21:56.878
TOM:
Shut up and get in.

22:17.880 --> 22:20.315
Got a real Cadillac here.

22:20.520 --> 22:22.238
Don't see steamboats too much
anymore.

22:24.320 --> 22:25.754
Our papers should be in order.

22:34.400 --> 22:35.959
You don't mind if we look around?

22:36.160 --> 22:37.878
Just a formality?

22:38.680 --> 22:40.512
Be my guest.

22:48.760 --> 22:50.398
ETHAN: Unh.
- What are you doing?

22:50.560 --> 22:52.517
They're not taking him back alive.

22:52.720 --> 22:56.395
If Georgia can't have him, no one can.

23:14.280 --> 23:15.600
Shh.

23:56.280 --> 23:57.600
JOHNSON:
Well, uh...

23:58.480 --> 24:03.156
...I'm afraid my associate found this.

24:05.400 --> 24:07.869
Now, you know ordnance are illegal.

24:10.360 --> 24:12.078
What are we gonna do about it?

24:16.360 --> 24:17.919
[SCOFFS]

24:18.360 --> 24:21.000
Look, if there's any way
we can let this slide...

24:27.600 --> 24:29.511
Don't let it happen again.

24:35.560 --> 24:37.551
Have a nice day.

24:42.280 --> 24:43.350
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

24:43.520 --> 24:44.635
RICHARD:
Major, we're clear.

24:54.600 --> 24:55.795
[TOM GRUNTS]

25:03.280 --> 25:05.112
TOM:
Get over there.

25:07.120 --> 25:08.599
Little bitch.

25:08.920 --> 25:09.955
You put a gun to my head?

25:10.120 --> 25:11.554
[GRUNTS]

25:16.040 --> 25:19.158
You ever touch her again,
I will snap your pencil neck.

25:20.240 --> 25:21.674
You get me?

25:26.520 --> 25:27.749
[THUD]

25:40.840 --> 25:42.831
[GUNSHOTS]

25:58.520 --> 26:00.158
[GUN CLICKING]

26:08.320 --> 26:09.799
- Where's your friend?
RACHEL: Please.

26:10.440 --> 26:11.510
No.

26:12.440 --> 26:14.431
[GRUNTING AND YELLING]

26:36.160 --> 26:38.151
[BOTH PANTING]

26:46.760 --> 26:48.478
You Okay?

26:48.640 --> 26:50.631
[CHUCKLES]

26:51.320 --> 26:53.038
Yeah.

27:13.800 --> 27:16.440
This has gone way too far,
you know that, right?

27:17.440 --> 27:19.556
MILES:
Come on, don't--

27:19.760 --> 27:21.637
Don't you start in on me too.

27:21.800 --> 27:24.633
Neville almost killed the guy.

27:26.120 --> 27:29.158
- We gotta cut him loose.
- No.

27:31.120 --> 27:33.475
- He could end up back with Monroe.
- Miles.

27:33.640 --> 27:35.995
You're holding a gun
against his daughter's head...

27:36.160 --> 27:38.913
...so you can blackmail him
into making a disease.

27:39.080 --> 27:42.072
How is this any different
than what Monroe did to my mom?

27:42.240 --> 27:43.639
Well, it's not.

27:45.440 --> 27:47.829
It's not any different.

27:49.720 --> 27:51.631
You think I wanna be doing this, Charlie?

27:56.000 --> 27:58.116
Ran as far away as I could.

27:58.320 --> 28:01.597
Tried to drink myself to death
so I wouldn't have to be this guy again.

28:05.160 --> 28:06.719
But this is--

28:08.680 --> 28:10.990
- This is war.
- No. Don't give me that.

28:11.640 --> 28:12.994
I get what war is.

28:13.160 --> 28:15.993
There are a lot of things
I'm willing to do to win. Not this.

28:16.160 --> 28:18.436
Well, there's nothing Monroe won't do!

28:18.600 --> 28:20.273
Nothing!

28:20.480 --> 28:22.232
He's coming for me, personally.

28:22.400 --> 28:23.799
Look what he did, Charlie.

28:24.000 --> 28:25.911
To our family.

28:26.200 --> 28:28.555
Look what he did to my town, to--

28:30.360 --> 28:31.759
Look what he did to Emma.

28:38.440 --> 28:40.875
I don't know, you tell me, Charlie.

28:41.040 --> 28:42.633
What choice do I have?

28:46.760 --> 28:50.196
Let these people go, Miles.

28:52.440 --> 28:54.033
No.

29:11.640 --> 29:13.517
[KEYS CLANGING]

29:16.640 --> 29:18.199
Charlie.

29:20.800 --> 29:22.518
Charlie, open this door.

29:22.680 --> 29:24.318
Open the door!

29:27.800 --> 29:29.791
Damn it, Charlie, open this door!

29:29.960 --> 29:31.951
[GRUNTING]

29:45.200 --> 29:46.235
[DOOR CLOSES]

29:48.760 --> 29:51.195
- So is Miles gonna help us?
- No.

29:53.320 --> 29:55.118
Okay, let's go.

30:00.400 --> 30:01.595
[GUN COCKS]

30:09.000 --> 30:11.560
Gentlemen, change of plans.

30:11.720 --> 30:13.119
CHARLIE:
Hey!

30:14.920 --> 30:18.151
Now, where's Dr. Camp's family?

30:25.440 --> 30:27.431
[SOBBING]

30:36.640 --> 30:39.871
Captain. Major Neville's boat,
dead in the water, sir. No one aboard.

30:48.240 --> 30:50.277
All right, let's check it out.

31:09.760 --> 31:11.319
Hey, guys.

31:12.680 --> 31:14.239
Move back.

31:15.320 --> 31:16.435
Move.

31:25.200 --> 31:27.316
[ERICA & BONNIE YELLING]

31:28.880 --> 31:29.950
Daddy!

31:30.560 --> 31:31.675
We gotta hurry.

31:32.520 --> 31:34.670
Okay. Stay here.

32:01.720 --> 32:03.677
- Thank you.
- We're not out of the woods yet.

32:03.840 --> 32:07.196
We're gonna take this boat to Dunbar,
2O miles up. I got friends there.

32:07.400 --> 32:09.357
- They're gonna help you disappear.
- Okay.

32:14.280 --> 32:15.953
[GUN COCKS]

32:17.560 --> 32:19.278
Give me the gun, boy.

32:20.600 --> 32:21.715
Give it to me.

32:24.520 --> 32:26.238
RICHARD:
Drop your weapon.

32:26.880 --> 32:28.075
Let's go.

32:30.240 --> 32:31.639
Move.

32:40.800 --> 32:44.236
I swear to Christ Almighty,
I will never understand...

32:44.440 --> 32:48.593
...how my own flesh and blood
could turn against me the way you have.

32:49.080 --> 32:50.878
Isn't it obvious?

32:51.600 --> 32:52.670
I hate you.

32:55.840 --> 32:56.910
[GRUNTS]

33:08.080 --> 33:10.071
[GUN COCKS]

33:12.480 --> 33:13.550
TOM:
I have to say...

33:15.160 --> 33:19.711
...you are the most irritable
pain in the ass I have ever known.

33:21.560 --> 33:22.789
[GRUNTS]

33:22.960 --> 33:25.031
- I told you not to touch her again.
- Unh!

33:26.840 --> 33:28.194
Uh-uh.

33:28.400 --> 33:29.879
Shoot them all.

33:30.040 --> 33:31.314
Sir, are you sure?

33:31.880 --> 33:33.678
Now.

33:35.280 --> 33:37.556
[GUNFIRE]

33:56.400 --> 33:59.677
You found Matheson. Why didn't you
take him when you had the chance?

33:59.840 --> 34:02.798
Think I'm gonna get into a straight fight
with Miles Matheson?

34:02.960 --> 34:03.995
Keep firing!

34:50.719 --> 34:53.030
[MAN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

35:05.880 --> 35:07.871
[ALL CHUCKLE]

35:24.520 --> 35:25.999
Thanks, Miles.

35:29.560 --> 35:33.394
No. Thank you.

35:47.400 --> 35:49.755
[GUNS COCK]

35:52.200 --> 35:55.033
Hey, Torn, you look upset.

35:55.520 --> 35:57.079
Go to hell, Miles.

35:57.240 --> 35:58.355
[SIGHS]

35:58.520 --> 35:59.555
How'd you get away?

36:00.320 --> 36:02.038
It cost me all my men to do it.

36:05.160 --> 36:06.195
Where's Dr. Camp?

36:06.360 --> 36:07.998
Oh, he's gone.

36:09.600 --> 36:11.910
I Will find him.

36:12.080 --> 36:13.753
You know I will.

36:14.400 --> 36:16.073
No, you won't.

36:16.920 --> 36:18.240
Wanna know why?

36:18.440 --> 36:20.875
Because I'm smarter than you are.

36:23.280 --> 36:27.956
He's not gonna work for Monroe
or for Foster.

36:33.040 --> 36:34.599
Fine.

36:37.040 --> 36:41.079
I'll take all the troops back to Georgia.

36:42.360 --> 36:44.112
Yeah, I kind of doubt that too.

36:45.480 --> 36:48.677
See, Tom, I'm winning.

36:50.120 --> 36:52.191
More battles all the time.

36:53.800 --> 36:55.871
And at the end of the day...

36:56.160 --> 36:58.674
...what do you think Foster
cares more about...

36:59.360 --> 37:03.911
...your pride or a win?

37:35.280 --> 37:36.759
NORA:
Hey.

37:40.120 --> 37:41.872
You still leaving?

37:43.200 --> 37:45.237
You want to hear a secret?

37:52.400 --> 37:53.470
Okay.

37:59.880 --> 38:02.554
You're not such a bad guy, Miles.

38:04.240 --> 38:08.029
Don't worry. I won't tell.

38:28.800 --> 38:30.791
[MOANING]

38:43.920 --> 38:45.240
RACHEL:
About what I said...

38:46.680 --> 38:48.353
It's okay.

38:50.360 --> 38:51.919
You didn't mean it.

38:53.880 --> 38:54.995
I meant some of it.

38:55.160 --> 38:58.391
- You have to go.
- Rachel, enough.

38:58.840 --> 39:03.550
Look. There is no one who wanted
to turn the power back on more than me.

39:03.720 --> 39:05.631
- You don't understand.
- But you know what?

39:05.800 --> 39:08.872
I'm beginning to think that maybe
there are some things...

39:09.040 --> 39:11.031
...that are a bit more important than that.

39:11.240 --> 39:14.278
You don't understand. What's important
is that you go to the Tower.

39:14.440 --> 39:16.397
You, Aaron.

39:18.920 --> 39:20.558
What does that mean?

39:21.640 --> 39:24.029
Dr. Warren's journal
is everything about the Tower.

39:24.200 --> 39:25.554
It's like a spell book.

39:30.720 --> 39:33.917
Open it. Page 74.

39:36.640 --> 39:38.438
I don't understand this, either.

39:39.880 --> 39:41.473
I didn't want to freak you out.

39:49.000 --> 39:50.752
AARON:
This is me.

39:52.440 --> 39:55.034
Rachel, why am I in this book?

39:59.720 --> 40:02.394
What do I have to do with any of this?

40:07.880 --> 40:09.871
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

40:23.560 --> 40:25.517
Elevator's up.

40:26.800 --> 40:28.029
It's about time.

40:32.800 --> 40:34.791
They can get us down to Level 12?

40:45.520 --> 40:47.477
You're gonna wait here.

40:49.400 --> 40:50.799
And I'm gonna take a look.

40:57.880 --> 41:00.394
Randall wouldn't want you down there.

41:00.600 --> 41:02.989
Yeah, well, he isn't here, is he?

41:16.040 --> 41:17.599
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGING]

41:39.440 --> 41:40.839
<i>Why'd it stop, Grace?</i>

41:42.720 --> 41:44.916
<i>I'm not in the mood for games.</i>

41:50.880 --> 41:53.190
[AUSTIN GRUNTING THEN SCREAMS]

41:58.720 --> 42:00.631
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGING]

42:04.720 --> 42:06.870
[GRACE WHIMPERING]

42:53.880 --> 42:55.871
[English - US - SDH]
